# A data:image literal on <a href> is a strict (non-image) sink: urlWriterMethod
# returns "URL", not "URLImage", so a statically-visible `data:` first segment is
# always author error (the runtime would just fail closed to
# about:invalid#gsx). Codegen rejects it up front, pointing at gsx.RawURL.
-- input.gsx --
package p

component Bad(png []byte) {
	<a href=f`data:image/png;base64,@{png}`>x</a>
}
-- diagnostics.golden --
4:5: data: URL literal in attribute "href" on <a> is a navigational/script sink where data: is blocked; use an image sink (<img src>, <video poster>, background) or gsx.RawURL if you have validated it
